messages.content: whoa! that sounds fun, though. I'm doing well. the transition from school to summer has been difficult, saying goodbye to folks and moving and such, but I feel really lucky to be where I am and have so many friends around this summer. I'm a research intern at a nonprofit that I think is awesome in Boston. I'm nervous for graduating in a year, but trying not to think about that too much. I'd love to see you if you're around Boston and hear about your adventures in Costa Rica!
I might be around Boston some points during summer so I'd def be down to hang
How are you doing?
Miss our pet convos too
Going to costa rica for summer as a guide for some voluntouring high school kids (hypocritcially working for the industry i rail against)
Hey Sophie! So so good to hear from you

Hey Kene! Congratulations on graduating! I hope you had a great year. What are your plans for the future? I would love to catch up if you're in the New England area. Sorry I've been so out of touch. I think about our conversation about pets frequently and often tell people about it to see their reactions. It's really interesting. I hope you're doing well.
hmmm good point. no I was just curious.
you tryna get into photography?
(also useful in countering our speciesist tendencies, although it's more commonly voyeuristic)
animal photography is dope. super expensive to do though, gear wise
what's up with the ugly webpage though
they're pretty nice!

hi. these photos were at first unimpressive, but then I kind of got into them. what do you think of animals being photographed? http://www.photosofthedays.com/29/148096023359/idFMBICJRBJLTV?p=NjE0OTY1MjA0MQ%3D%3D&hl=en_US
hah I'm fine. I'm semi-excited fro the semester. mostly to have my own home and cook my own food and invite friends over. let me know how yours goes too.
Ouch. Hope you're not emotionally scarred or cynophobic now. Glad you're excited about school again. Lemme know how the semester turns out!

I'm totally okay. I just have two big scrapes on my legs. It was very weird. I don't usually expect peoples pets to want to hurt me. I don't start classes until the 8th, but I'm moving in on monday. I'm kind of excited to be back.
I miss our arguments :)
I get into campus next week. Hope you're enjoying, or at least tolerating, classes too
I would gloat but that sounds terrible
Sophie! Hope you're not wounded!

Hey Kene! My friend's dog attacked me yesterday and reminded me of our conversations about pets. I don't think many people feel the way that you do, but honestly your argument has merit. I hope you are well and off to a good start at school.

Oh no! You probably left. I'm sorry I've been so out of touch I don't really have access to the internet. Are you back in ny? If you ever want to visit Boston you are always welcome to stay in my apartment.
But I should be able to squeeze something in if you wanna meet up (lets!)
Wrapping up experiments and prepping to for presentations/ writing paper tho so my schedule is pretty tight
Yeah I'm around until Friday next week
Happy Birthday! Hope you make the most of the best decade of life (you're turning 20 right?)

are you around this week?
